claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Page 1 of the Flublok full prescribing information showing section headings (table of contents), dosage and administration instructions (single 0.5 mL dose), dosage forms and strengths, contraindications, warnings, and adverse reactions. does not support the claim – the visible contents include dosing instructions and safety information but do not present any data on hemagglutinin antigen content or comparisons to standard-dose vaccines.
